    {
        "content": "<p>Hello everyone, I had a question regarding proving a contradiction in lean4. In this scenario, I have the hypothesis h1: a^4 + b^4 = c^4 and the goal: a^4 + b^4 ≠ c^4. I tried using By.contradiction but it does not work. Any idea on how to proceed with this?</p>",
        "id": 457350008,
        "sender_full_name": "Rohan Joshi",
        "timestamp": 1723119005
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>This is not a logically correct argument</p>",
        "id": 457350327,
        "sender_full_name": "Ruben Van de Velde",
        "timestamp": 1723119137
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Given a hypothesis that 1 = 1, you cannot prove that 1 \\ne 1</p>",
        "id": 457350352,
        "sender_full_name": "Ruben Van de Velde",
        "timestamp": 1723119155
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>it will need to be concluded from other hypotheses.</p>",
        "id": 457350425,
        "sender_full_name": "Edward van de Meent",
        "timestamp": 1723119190
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"731228\">Rohan Joshi</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/113489-new-members/topic/showing.20contradiction/near/457350008\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>In this scenario, I have the hypothesis h1: a^4 + b^4 = c^4 and the goal: a^4 + b^4 ≠ c^4.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Is <code>h1</code> the only hypothesis you have?</p>",
        "id": 457350430,
        "sender_full_name": "Bulhwi Cha",
        "timestamp": 1723119194
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>no, I have hypotheses :<br>\nh: a^4 + b^4 = c^4 \\im \\exists d, a^4 + b^4 = d^2 \\and a<em>b</em>d \\neq 0<br>\nh2: \\exists d, a^4 + b^4  = d^2 \\and a<em>b</em>d \\neq 0</p>",
