    {
        "content": "<p>regarding the <code>Exists.elim</code>, what you can do if you have a <code>h : ∃ (d:SomeType), some_prop d</code> is use <code>obtain ⟨d,hd⟩ := h2</code>, which adds <code>d:SomeType</code> and <code>hd : some_prop d</code> to the context.</p>",
        "id": 457363936,
        "sender_full_name": "Edward van de Meent",
        "timestamp": 1723121998
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>btw, using <code>variable (d: ℤ)</code> in this case is more harmful than good, because you don't want <em>any</em> integer <code>d</code>, but specifically <em>the one you proved exists with the property you want</em></p>",
        "id": 457364452,
        "sender_full_name": "Edward van de Meent",
        "timestamp": 1723122118
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>and having multiple integers <code>d</code> floating around only leads to confusion</p>",
